    "assumptions": [
      "Caching: when definitionIds is provided, getPressureSensitivityResult skips the assumptionAnalysisSnapshot cache entirely and computes synchronously. Per-pair scope is small enough to compute in-request; per-pair cache rows would proliferate.",
      "Route: /vignette/:definitionId/paired. Definition-centric URL signals the move away from run-centric analysis.",
      "Companion lookup: db.definition.findFirst with matching methodology.pair_key (JSONB path) and different components.value_first.token, deletedAt: null. Tie-breaker on multiple matches: most recent createdAt, with a warn log for the pair_key uniqueness gap.",
      "Single-direction case: when no companion exists, the page renders self-side data with a banner naming the missing direction. This is a real product state, not an error.",
      "Signature default: derived from the definition's most recent completed run's signature (existing pattern). Overridable via ?signature= query param like PressureSensitivity page.",
      "Condition drilldown stays run-scoped for v1 \u2014 AnalysisConditionDetail is unchanged. The new vignette page is a summary view.",
      "Glossary terms: vignette, condition, attribute, direction, trial. Existing legacy code may still say definition/dimension/scenario; map rather than rename."
    ],
    "summary": "Vignette-first paired analysis report. Replace run-centric paired analysis with vignette-pair-centric report by adding an optional definitionIds argument to the existing pressureSensitivity GraphQL query, threading it through preparePressureSensitivityState to also pull the companion definition (same methodology.pair_key, different components.value_first.token), composing a thin new page that reuses existing PressureSensitivityDetail / PressureGrid / PressureSensitivitySummary / PressureResponseByValueTable components, linking to it from AnalysisDetail, and deleting PairedRunComparisonCard with its broken count-additive math. No new GraphQL types, no new aggregation, no new utilities, no new components, no new hooks, no new resolvers.",
    "updated_at": 1778013330,
    "answers": {},
    "non_goals": [
      "New aggregation math, new GraphQL types, new resolvers on Definition, new utility modules, new components, new hooks",
      "Per-pair snapshot caching (deferred \u2014 recompute in-request)",
      "JSONB GIN index on methodology.pair_key (deferred \u2014 companion lookup is one query per page load)",
      "pair_key uniqueness enforcement at the database level (deferred \u2014 log warning on multi-match)",
      "Migrating AnalysisConditionDetail.tsx to vignette-centric routing (stays run-scoped for v1)",
      "Backfill of companionRunId or pairedBatchGroupId for legacy runs",
      "Caching layer for vignette-paired view; reuse the synchronous compute path"
    ],
    "acceptance_criteria": [
      "pressureSensitivity GraphQL query accepts an optional definitionIds: [ID!] argument; when provided, eligible runs are filtered to those definitions plus the companion (resolved by pair_key match)",
      "New page at /vignette/:definitionId/paired loads, queries pressureSensitivity with definitionIds=[selfId], and renders one PressureSensitivityValuePair per model using existing PressureSensitivityDetail and PressureGrid components",
      "AnalysisDetail.tsx shows a 'View paired analysis' link to the new page when methodology.pair_key is present, and the legacy companion-search effect block (useInfiniteRuns fallback, directCompanionRun, companionRunWithTranscripts) is removed",
      "PairedRunComparisonCard.tsx is deleted along with buildComparisonRows, buildValueCounts, mergeWeightedSensitivity, findCompanionPairedRun, getRunConfigBatchGroupId, getDefinitionPairKey; no remaining imports of these symbols anywhere",
      "Regression test asserts that for a fixture with 100 trials in one direction and 10 in the other, the resulting direction-balanced win rate equals the equal-weight average per direction, not the count-weighted pooled rate",
      "Existing pressureSensitivity domain-scoped query path is unchanged (no behavior delta when definitionIds is null); existing snapshot cache writes/reads only on the domain-scoped path",
      "When the companion definition is missing, the new page renders self-side numbers with a clear banner; no error state, no silent gap"
    ],
